    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-07T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="399"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 763.72112/9762</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BBA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-07T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 11, 3.03 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s confidential August 3, 7 p.m. Result of conference held this morning
                    is that all German firms in Haiti are now being, or <pb facs="0447" n="363"
                        xml:id="pg_363"/> will be, sequestrated. Pursuant to presidential decree of
                    July 24 as to sequestration, forwarded in my No. 252 of July 27,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d399fn1">Not printed.</note> Maumus, receiver several [<hi
                        rend="italic">general</hi>], and Scarpa, director of the bank, were
                    appointed sequestrators by the Minister of Justice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BBA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
